
<acqabr>S. AND W. BERISFORD</acqabr> WANTS TO STAY INDEPENDENT
    LONDON, June 18 - <acquired>S.And W. Berisford Plc</acquired> {<acqcode>BRFD.L</acqcode>}, which
has attracted takeover bids, is <status>making every possible effort to
remain independent</status>, deputy chairman Henry Lewis said after the
company announced interim results.
    "We've taken specific steps to strengthen ourselves for this
purpose," he added, referring to management changes and a
corporate strategy of concentrating on four business sectors.
    <acqabr>Berisford</acqabr> aims to produced balanced earnings growth from a
combination of <acqbus>commodities, property, financial services and
food</acqbus>. Its industrial division, with assets of about 90 mln stg
including debt, is being reviewed and parts may be sold.
